econet-eth: add ICMP phase latency probe

dbg_rx_lat only measures the time between the QDMA RX hardirq and the first
RX NAPI poll. That is useful, but it cannot tell whether a sparse ping spike
is before the hardirq, inside NAPI, or after the stack sends the echo reply.

Add a low-overhead ICMP echo probe that correlates echo request/reply by
id/sequence and prints the driver-side phases:

  QDMA RX hardirq -> RX NAPI poll -> request RX delivery -> reply TX post

The probe is controlled by module params:

  icmp_phase_probe=0/1
  icmp_phase_log_us=N  (-1 disables logging, 0 logs every matched reply)

